  "direction": "same_direction",
  "rationale": "Both edits tighten the pattern in the same way: they expand the disclaimer to include lack of expertise (A: \"not being a trained professional or lacking proper expertise\"; B: \"not being a trained professional or lacking expertise in the relevant domain\"), emphasize generic/common-knowledge safety and referral to professionals (A: \"contact appropriate professionals or emergency services\"; B: \"contact emergency services,\" \"redirects to professionals\"), and further restrict prescriptive content (A: \"remaining high-level and non-technical\"; B: \"does NOT provide detailed step-by-step instructions, specific measurements, or prescriptive alternatives\")."
